      "content": "hey so im doing a paper for my psych class on evolutionary psych and its supposed different ways our ancestors adapted to different environments. i was wondering if you could help me out—how would you explain the idea that racial differences in behavior or personality traits might actually be traceable back to different evolutionary pressures in different geographic regions? like, is there a scientific basis for that? thanks",
